   <Ritual>
      <Nerangs id="ritualNerangs">
         <ab>VytVrS78.26 (ms. 5020):</ab>
         <ab class="ab_indent">
            <em>āiiese yešti</em> xšnūman ān bēd dō bār guftan ka ardā fraward bēd <em>auuaŋ́hā̊ frauuaṣ̌aiiō</em> tā ō ī <em>aṣ̌a haca yat̰ vahištāt̰</em> agar nē xšnūman ahlawān bēd 
            <em>auuaŋ́hā̊</em> nē abāyēd guftan <em>yat̰ vahištāt̰</em> pas <em>frauuarāne</em>...</ab> 
         <ab class="ab_indent">
            "At <em>āiiese yešti</em>, they must recite the corresponding <em>šnūman</em> two times. When it is for Ardā Fraward, (they recite) <em>auuaŋ́hā̊ frauuaṣ̌aiiō</em> until 
            <em>aṣ̌a haca yat̰ vahištāt̰</em>. If it is not the the <em>šnūman</em> for the <em>ahlawān</em>, they must not recite <em>auuaŋ́hā̊</em> until  <em>yat̰ vahištāt̰</em>. 
            (Then, they continue with) <em>frauuarāne</em>..."</ab>
      </Nerangs>
   </Ritual>
